Coca-Cola Nigeria has announced that it has consolidated its public relations accounts to be managed by Precise Platforms. The company stated that the relationship which would see the corporate and brand public relations accounts combined at the strategic communications agency came into force January 1, 2022.   ‘At 88, I am not tired’     Why Nigeria can’t meet OPEC quota – Sylva     Business leaders, experts rally entrepreneurs on…   Director, Public Affairs, Communications and Sustainability, Coca-Cola Nigeria, Nwamaka Onyemelukwe, said: “When we commenced the process of reviewing our PR strategy for 2022, we were focused on ensuring we deliver on our core objectives for the year, foremost of which was to continue to deliver our brand promise to both our consumers and valued stakeholders. With this in mind, we successfully consolidated our accounts, closing out 2021 very strong and with a lot of hope for 2022. “With the commencement of this new partnership with Precise Platforms, we are confident that our new team will continue to represent our interests in the most outstanding way and we remain optimistic that 2022 will be a truly rewarding year for both parties.” Managing Director, Precise Platforms, Bolaji Okusaga,  said: “We are delighted to earn this relationship with Coca-Cola Nigeria, a global leader in its segment. We are humbled by the valuable responsibility of lending expert perception minding support to the proven team at Coca-Cola.”